  {
    "title": "Information integrity crisis is an ‘existential challenge for humanity",
    "link": "https://media20.org/2026/07/09/information-integrity-crisis-is-an-existential-challenge-for-humanity/",
    "pubDate": "2026-07-09T06:34:15.000Z",
    "content": "<p><span>Former UNESCO </span><span>Director for Freedom of Expression and Media Development Guy Berger has issued a&nbsp; call for transparency from tech companies, and for algorithms to give prominence to quality information –&nbsp; “instead of recommending whatever ‘slop’ happens to grab attention”.</span></p>\n<p><span>In a strongly worded article published on the UNESCO website, Berger warned of the threats to information integrity and the urgent need to act.</span></p>\n<p><span>“Behemoth companies have monopolised massive audiences and the lion’s share of advertising revenue, while demonstrating a declining regard for information integrity. Media ventures, for their part, are left with dwindling funds, while algorithms penalize the visibility of news content on social media. Simultaneously, AI companies take journalists’ work without credit or compensation. The result is a fast-looming crisis.”</span></p>",
    "snippet": "Former UNESCO Director for Freedom of Expression and Media Development Guy Berger has issued a call for transparency from tech companies, and for algorithms to give prominence to quality information –",
    "creator": "Noor Ahmad",
    "sourceTitle": "Media20",
    "sheetCategory": "Digital Policy + Rights",
    "enforcedImage": "https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Guy-Berger.jpg",
    "sourceDescription": "",
    "sourceLogo": "https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/cropped-favicon2-32x32.png",
