    "title": "A licensed trust for African media data: Ubuntu as a blueprint for Africa’s AI economy",
    "link": "https://media20.org/2026/03/18/a-licensed-trust-for-african-media-data-ubuntu-as-a-blueprint-for-africas-ai-economy/",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-18T07:24:35.000Z",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%27http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%27%20width='1000'%20height='450'%20viewBox=%270%200%201000%20450%27%3E%3C/svg%3E\" loading=\"lazy\" data-lazy=\"1\" width=\"1000\" height=\"450\" data-tf-src=\"https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels.png\" class=\"tf_svg_lazy attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" data-tf-srcset=\"https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels.png 1000w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-300x135.png 300w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-768x346.png 768w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-1280x576.png 1280w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-500x225.png 500w\" data-tf-sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"><noscript><img width=\"1000\" height=\"450\" data-tf-not-load src=\"https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels.png 1000w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-300x135.png 300w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-768x346.png 768w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-1280x576.png 1280w, https://media20.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/M20-article-_Jep-Gambardella-Pexels-500x225.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></noscript></p>\n<p><i><span>By Barbra Okafor </span></i></p>\n<p>When <i>Papaoutai</i> came through my feed during AFCON, I stopped scrolling. The swell of voices, the Afro Soul style, and the emotion behind it felt like a real discovery. Whoever made this, I thought, is about to have a moment.</p>\n<p><span>Then I looked it up.</span></p>",
